quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  23,23,"Indeed, We sent Noah to his people. He declared, ‚ÄúO my people! Worship Allah ňĻaloneňļ. You have no god other than Him. Will you not then fear ňĻHimňļ?‚ÄĚ"
  23,24,"But the disbelieving chiefs of his people said ňĻto the massesňļ, ‚ÄúThis is only a human like you, who wants to be superior to you. Had Allah willed, He could have easily sent down angels ňĻinsteadňļ. We have never heard of this in ňĻthe history ofňļ our forefathers"
  23,25,"He is simply insane, so bear with him for a while.‚ÄĚ"
  23,26,"Noah prayed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Help me, because they have denied ňĻmeňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  23,27,"So We inspired him: ‚ÄúBuild the Ark under Our ňĻwatchfulňļ Eyes and directions. Then when Our command comes and the oven bursts ňĻwith waterňļ,¬†take on board a pair from every species along with your family‚ÄĒexcept those against whom the decree ňĻto drownňļ has already been passed. And do not plead with Me for those who have done wrong, for they will surely be drowned.‚ÄĚ"
  23,28,"Then when you and those with you have settled in the Ark, say, ‚ÄúAll praise is for Allah, Who saved us from the wrongdoing people.‚ÄĚ"
  23,29,"And pray, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Allow me a blessed landing, for You are the best accommodator.‚ÄĚ"
  23,30,Surely in this are lessons.¬†And We ňĻalwaysňļ put ňĻpeopleňļ to the test
  23,31,Then We raised another generation after them
  23,32,"and sent to them a messenger from among themselves, ňĻdeclaring,ňļ ‚ÄúWorship Allah ňĻaloneňļ. You have no god other than Him. Will you not then fear ňĻHimňļ?‚ÄĚ"